.TH RUN_IN_TERM "1" "December 2025" "run_in_term 202208151859-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
run_in_term \- Keep a terminal application running
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B run_in_term
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,ARGUMENTS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B run_in_term
is a script that runs a command in a terminal window and keeps the terminal open after the command completes. It prevents the terminal from closing immediately after execution.
.PP
The script is useful for running commands from desktop shortcuts or menus where you want to see the output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-term
Explicitly open in a terminal window
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B run_in_term ls -la
List files and keep terminal open
.TP
.B run_in_term ./build.sh
Run build script with visible output
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/run_in_term/settings.conf
User configuration file for run_in_term preferences
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 3
Command not found
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Opens command in terminal emulator
.IP \(bu 2
Waits for user input before closing
.IP \(bu 2
Useful for desktop integration
